	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=57570><span id=Guru>Niteklaw</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>357 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.55]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The IBC is in my opinion MUCH too heavy for a monk (8.0), the STR-bonus is nice, but the WIS is useles and the proc doesn't go off until lvl 30, I believe. IF you actually got your hands on an Iksar Berserker Club, I would suggest that you sell it. If you get a price anywhere near the prices reported (9,000+pp) you can get yourself almost ANY monk weapon you might like with money to spare. (Incidently, I know from personal experience that getting this club is VERY difficult).<br><br>2 FBs isn't bad, but maybe consider an Essence of Dol for the offhand (pack a bit more of a punch than the FB, and it's cheaper, though a bit slower). If you have lots of cash to throw around, the Fighting Baton/Cane of the Tranquil-combo is very popular and will do you nicely well into your forties.<br><br>Niteklaw "20+ hours of camping the Jester in Kurn's and still no IBC" Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk, Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=akztarg><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></td></tr>
