	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>680 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Niteklaw makes a point that defines monks - weight is king.&nbsp;&nbsp;The IBC is a nice weapon, but in fact an FB will out-perform an IBC until level 30 or so, and it costs 500 p instead of a few thousand (the price has dropped drastically on my server - maybe 3k), and at 8 pounds, it'll clobber your AC.  2 Fighting Batons is clearly a better choice. <br><br>For your off hand weapon, Cane of Tranquil &gt; Fighting Baton &gt; Essence of Dol.  In your off-hand all that matters is damage ratio, which goes by (damage*2+1)/delay.  The Essence of Dol hits harder than a baton, but is much slower, and in the end you do fewer points/sec of damage.  Its only benefits over an FB are its lower cost and zero weight - if you're having weight issues, it can save you AC.  Get what you can afford.  If you do in fact get a CoT/FB, you'll do better with CoT primary and FB off-hand until lvl 35, when you should switch them to take advantage of the primary hand bonus.  Weapon combos for monks can get confusing and tricky, so I'll stop here (things get weirder in your 40s) because you're talking about just starting out a monkey.  <br><br>Oh, and one more note - It's not easy to farm items that sell for thousands of plat.  The reason they sell for so much cash is that they are not only in demand but rare, and that implies rare spawns and rare drops.  People do farm things, but realize that it's not a quick and simple proposition.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
